                    <li><strong>Relevance:</strong> not just provide information that is important to the business purpose. When irrelevant information is reported, business intelligence reporting centres on action-oriented insights.</li>
                    <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> To follow consistency, consistency means that reports are to be reported conventionally and in the same way all the time. This enables it to be similar across history, and a lot of fashions are being tracked due to the involvement of the automated reporting systems.</li>
